is accounts of Jewish tenement residents echoed with the mistakes and malapropisms born of the immigrant experience.Introduced by an historical essay, Is Diss a System? presents some of the most outstanding and hilarious examples of Jewish dialect humor drawn from the five books Gross published between 1926 and 1928-Nize Baby, De Night in de Front from Chreesmas, Hiawatta, Dunt Esk, and Famous Fimmales-providing a fresh opportunity to look, read, and laugh at this nearly forgotten forefather of American Jewish humor.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aAmerican wit and humor, Pictorial. 0aCaricatures and cartoonszUnited States. 0aComic books, strips, etczUnited States. 0aComic books, strips, etc.zUnited States. 0aJewish wit and humor, Pictorial. 7aHUMOR / Form / Comic Strips & Cartoons.2bisacsh  a1926.  a1928.  aDiss.  aGross.  aIntroduced.  aJewish.  aSystem.  abetween.  abooks.  adialect.  adrawn.  aessay.  aexamples.  afive.  afrom.  ahilarious.  ahistorical.  ahumor.  amost.  aoutstanding.  apresents.  apublished.  asome.1 aKelman, Ari Y., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKelman, Ari Y., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070644440uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9780814749142.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814749142423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780814749142/original  a978-3-11-070644-4  New York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles